content: The AI Conference 2025 FAQ. These are the most frequently asked questions about The AI Conference 2025. If you don't see an answer you’re looking for, email us at info@aiconference.com and we’ll be happy to assist you!
overview: Introduction to the FAQ section for The AI Conference 2025 and provides contact information for further assistance.

content: Can I attend this event virtually? This is an in-person event only. We promote community and networking and hope to see you there.
overview: Answers the question about virtual attendance, confirming the event is in-person only.

content: Where is this event located? This is an in-person event at Pier 48, Mission Rock, San Francisco, CA 94158
overview: Provides the location of the in-person event: Pier 48, San Francisco.

content: When is the event? The AI Conference takes place on SEPTEMBER 17th – 18th, 2025 beginning at 8:00 AM PST.
overview: Specifies the dates and starting time of The AI Conference 2025.

content: How can my company sponsor The AI Conference? Please visit: aiconference.com/sponsors/ for all exhibitor opportunities.
overview: Provides a link to the sponsorship information page for exhibitor opportunities.

content: Where can I park My Car? The most up to date parking info can be found at Park Wiz https://www.parkwhiz.com/pier-48-parking/?daily=1
overview: Provides a link to ParkWiz for up-to-date parking information near the event venue.

content: How much does The AI Conference 2025 cost? The conference has Early Bird pricing while supplies last. For those who miss our early pricing, the current price of the standard passes can be found on the registration page after launch.
overview: Details the pricing structure, mentioning Early Bird pricing and standard pass prices available on the registration page.

content: Under what circumstances do you offer discounts? Group rates are available to groups of three or more attendees registering together. Contact tickets@aiconference.com to receive a group rate discount code.
overview: Explains the availability of group rates for attendees and provides the contact email for obtaining a discount code.

content: Do you offer discounts or complimentary passes? For groups of two or more people registering together, discounted group rates are available. To obtain a discount code for group rates, please contact tickets@aiconference.com
overview: Reiterates the availability of discounted group rates and provides the contact email for obtaining a discount code.

content: What is the Cancellation policy? The AI Conference offers refunds up to 30 days prior to an event. A fee of 5% will be charged for all refunds. Email tickets@aiconference.com for refund requests.
overview: Outlines the cancellation policy, including the refund timeframe and associated fees, and provides the email for refund requests.

content: Is there a code of conduct? Please view our code of conduct at aiconference.com/code-of-conduct/
overview: Directs users to the conference's code of conduct page.

content: I have a press, vendor, or speaker pass. What now? The AI Conference will be sending a series of emails that include everything needed to navigate the event including information about meals, transportation, maps, and tips and tricks to getting the most out of your experience.
overview: Explains that attendees with special passes will receive a series of emails with event information.

content: Can I present at the conference? We will open submissions for this year’s conference speakers soon. Be sure to sign up for our speakers interest list https://aiconference.com/cfp/ to be notified.
overview: Informs potential speakers about upcoming submission opportunities and provides a link to the speakers interest list.

content: How do I get a press pass? If you are a member of the press, you can apply for a media pass shortly.
overview: Indicates that press passes will be available for application soon.

content: Who will be speaking at the conference? 2 DAYS | 4 TRACKS | 85+ SPEAKERS Our ever updating list of speakers, presenters, and sponsors can be found at aiconference.com
overview: Provides information about the number of speakers and tracks, and directs users to the website for an updated list.

content: How long will presentations be? Presentations will be broken into 3 types: Keynote presentations lasting 40 minutes and featured contributors with a duration of 20 minutes. Vendor and sponsor presentations may vary in time and may be revisited throughout the duration of the conference.
overview: Details the duration of different types of presentations at the conference.

content: What topics will be covered? A wide range of topics will be covered including: AGI development, Foundation Models and Large Language Models, Generative AI, Neural Architectures, AI Infrastructure, AI Use Cases, Ethics and Alignment, Data Management tools for AI, AI Startups & Investment, and more.
overview: Lists the various topics that will be covered during the conference.

content: Are there multiple presentation areas? There are 4 main areas at The AI Conference. Four presentation halls, a vendor and sponsor presentation area, and an atrium area where networking mixers and food & beverages are served. In addition there are multiple indoor and outdoor networking areas with tables for dining and networking. Information on the four is found here: Tracks https://aiconference.com/#tracks
overview: Describes the different presentation and networking areas available at the conference and provides a link to more information about the tracks.
